The Kenya Bureau of Standards has suspended the production of Dasani water at Coca Cola Company s Kikambala plant in Kilifi County.This follows a visit by KEBS officers at the plant after members of the Mombasa County Assembly reported on Tuesday that they found pieces of wool in Dasani branded drinking water. Read: Cotton wool found in Dasani water in MombasaKEBS regional manager Martin Nyakiamo said the suspension will remain effective until after surveillance inspectors give a clean bill of health to the said production line.The regional manager further clarified that they will ensure that no substandard water will be marketed in the region.The Coca Cola company has forthwith recalled the units that were bottled between September 16 and 18, 2016.The 6500 half liter bottles were to be distributed in the Coast region.